==English==

===Etymology===
French '''chagrin''', possibly from French ''[[chagraigner]]''

===Pronunciation===
*[[AHD]]: shə-grĭn'
*{{audio|en-us-chagrin.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Noun===
'''chagrin'''
#(uncountable) [[annoyance]], [[vexation]] or [[discouragement]]
#:''He noted with '''chagrin''' the mounting pile of unfinished homework.''

====Translations====
{{top}}
{{mid}}
*Russian: [[досада|доса́да]] (dosáda) {{f}}, [[огорчение|огорче́ние]] (ogorchénie) {{n}}
{{bottom}}

===Transitive verb===
'''chagrin'''
# to [[bother]] or [[vex]]
#:''She was '''chagrinned''' to note that the paint had dried into a blotchy mess.''

====Translations====
{{top}}
{{mid}}
*Russian: [[досаждать|досажда́ть]] (dosaždát'), [[огорчать|огорча́ть]] (ogorčát')
{{bottom}}

